					Full Description



TRI Pointe Group, Inc., incorporated on May 28, 2015, is a homebuilder company. The Company's operations are organized in two principal businesses, including homebuilding and financial services. Its homebuilding operation consists of six segments: Maracay Homes, including operations in Arizona; Pardee Homes, consisting of operations in California and Nevada; Quadrant Homes, consisting of operations in Washington; Trendmaker Homes, consisting of operations in Texas; TRI Pointe Homes, consisting of operations in California and Colorado, and Winchester Homes, consisting of operations in Maryland and Virginia. Its financial services operation (TRI Pointe Solutions) includes mortgage financing operations and title services operations. Its mortgage financing operation (TRI Pointe Connect) provides mortgage financing to its homebuyers in all of its operated markets. Its title services operation (TRI Pointe Assurance) provides title examinations for its homebuyers in its Trendmaker Homes and Winchester Homes brands. TRI Pointe Assurance is a subsidiary of the Company. As of December 31, 2016, the Company's operations consisted of 124 active selling communities, and 28,309 lots, which are owned or controlled by the Company.As of December 31, 2016, the Company had six homebuilding brands operating in 14 markets across eight states. The brands include Maracay Homes in Arizona, Pardee Homes in California and Nevada, Quadrant Homes in Washington, Trendmaker Homes in Texas, TRI Pointe Homes in California and Colorado, and Winchester Homes in Maryland and Virginia. The Company's Maracay Homes brand has various projects under development, including Verrado Tilden, Verrado Palisades, Verrado Victory, Artesian Ranch, Vaquero Ranch, Sendera Place, Marquis at Morrison Ranch, Adora Trails, The Reserve at Plaza del Rio, The Preserve at Hastings Farms, Navarro Groves and Maracay at Northlands.The Company's Pardee Homes brand has projects under development, including Alta Del Mar Homes, Watermark, Canterra, Casabella, Verana, Meadowood, Parkview Condos, South Otay Mesa, Ocean View Hills Future, Meadow Glen, Summerfield, Senterra, Skyline Ranch and Canyon Hills Future. The Company's projects under development in its Quadrant Homes brand include The Grove at Canyon Park, Bothell, Greenstone Heights, Bothell, Vintner's Place, Kirkland, Trailside, Redmond, Parkwood Terrace, Woodinville, English Landing P1, Redmond, Wynstone, Federal Way, Canton Crossing, Maple Valley, Breva, Bellevue, Cedar Landing, North Bend, Aurea, Sammamish, Campus Fairways, Lacey and Mountain Aire, Poulsbo.The Company's Trendmaker Homes brand has projects under development, including Sedona Lakes, Pearland, Pomona, Manvel, Rise Meridiana, Cinco Ranch, Katy, The Townhomes at Imperial, Sugar Land, Harborwalk, Hitchcock, Fairfield, Cypress, The Groves, Humble, Lakes of Creekside, Barton Woods, Conroe, Villas at Oakhurst, Porter, Woodtrace, Woodtrace, Northgrove, Tomball, The Woodlands, Creekside Park, Cane Island, Katy, Crystal Falls and Mustang Estates. Its TRI Pointe Homes has projects under development, including Arcadia, Irvine, Messina, Irvine, Alston, Anaheim, StrataPointe, Buena Park, Topazridge, Riverside, Aldea, Temecula, Grayson, Santa Clarita, Garvey Square, El Monte, Bradford @ Rosedale, Azusa, Derose, Morgan Hill, Green Valley-Lewis, Fairfield and Ventana, Tracy. The Company's Winchester Homes brand has projects under development, including Two Rivers, Crofton, Walnut Creek, Ellicott City, Cabin Branch, Clarksburg, Cabin Branch Boulevard Townhomes, Preserve at Stoney Spring, Poplar Run, Silver Spring, Potomac Highlands, Potomac, Reserve at Waples Mill, Oakton, Villages of Piedmont, Haymarket, English Manor Villas and Westbrook, Fairfax.

» Full Overview of TPH







