TPH - Market Data & News
TPH - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

TRI Pointe Group Inc. (TPH) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 28, as the stock 
lost 2.12% to close at $13.38. On the day, TRI Pointe Group Inc. saw 3.69 million shares trade hands on 14,676 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 1.89 million shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $14.21 and $10.35 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $12.96, and its 200-day SMA $12.34. TRI Pointe Group Inc. 
has a P/B ratio of 1.2. It also has a P/E ratio of 16.3.  


TRI Pointe Group Inc, formerly TRI Pointe Homes Inc is engaged in the design, construction and sale of single-family homes in metropolitan areas located throughout California and Colorado. The Company's segments are homebuilding and construction services.

Headquartered in Irvine, CA, TRI Pointe Group Inc. has 1,137 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Douglas F. Bauer.


For a complete fundamental analysis analysis of TRI Pointe Group Inc., check out Equities.com’s Stock Valuation Analysis report 
for TPH.

