Our Story

In 2009, Doug Bauer, Tom Mitchell and Mike Grubbs shared a vision and concept for a new kind of homebuilding company – one driven by home design that provides homebuyers and their families with a lifetime of experiences.


That year, the economic downturn crippled many industries. However, they recognized this time as an opportunity to bring their vision to life. They drew upon their 25+ years of homebuilding know-how to create TRI Pointe Homes. 


TRI Pointe Homes quickly became a publicly held company, trading under “TPH” on the NYSE. It was the first IPO in homebuilding to emerge after the downturn. Within 5 years, the company merged with Weyerhaeuser Real Estate Company (WRECO), which operated as five distinct homebuilding companies in seven states, to become TRI Pointe Group. This merger has created one of the top 10 largest public homebuilding companies in the United States based on equity market capitalization.








                2009
            





